org.tms.api

Interface Cell

  • All Superinterfaces:
    BaseElement, Derivable, Listenable, TableElement, Taggable

    public interface Cell
extends TableElement, Derivable
    A Table cell. Cells contain user data, as set by the variety of TMS Table, Row, Column, Subset, and Cell methods. Cells can also be set through derivations.

    Cells only exist in the context of Rows and Columns, and as such, there are no methods available to create and/or fetch them directly. That said, specific cells can be assigned labels and can be added to Subsets. Cells are only created when there is non-null data to assign to them.

    Since:
    "1.0"
    Version:
    "1.1"
